title: Problems in American Democracy
creator: Thames Williamson
description: LibriVox recording of Problems in American Democracy by Thames Willianson, read by Allyson Hester. Problems in American Democracy is a very detailed, specific explanation of some of the underlying and surface problems of a democracy system of government, particularly of the American form of democracy. Though lengthy, it is a great read for people who want to learn more about different types of government and the foundations of our own government in the United States of America.
